    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add your <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a piece of<strong> tin foil</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and seal the foil tightly around them</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saucy-bbq-double-chicken-breast-with-wedges-and-corn/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>foil-wrapped cobettes</strong> to the tray[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the wedges are crispy</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saucy-bbq-double-chicken-breast-with-wedges-and-corn/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> ground cumin</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> to a plate and mix to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>spice rub</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saucy-bbq-double-chicken-breast-with-wedges-and-corn/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> to the plate and turn several times until evenly coated in the spices</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saucy-bbq-double-chicken-breast-with-wedges-and-corn/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saucy-bbq-double-chicken-breast-with-wedges-and-corn/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once golden, reduce the heat to low, then add your <strong>BBQ sauce</strong> and 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml]</span> <strong>water </strong>to the pan</p><p>Mix it together and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>BBQ chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saucy-bbq-double-chicken-breast-with-wedges-and-corn/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, add your<strong> cider vinegar</strong> to a large bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and add it to the bowl, gently tossing with the dressing \u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saucy-bbq-double-chicken-breast-with-wedges-and-corn/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>BBQ chicken</strong> with the <strong>potato wedges</strong>, <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> and <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>BBQ chicken</strong> with the <strong>remaining BBQ sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
